Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.11,0:01:39.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's much more serene compared to yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.37,0:01:44.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The waters around here are real technicolor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.24,0:01:46.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a masterpiece once you dive in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:47.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.41,0:01:50.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've done some scuba diving at Ishigaki Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.58,0:01:52.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:55.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like a real yuppie bachelor's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.30,0:01:57.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that great.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:02:01.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Putting this beer to my lips in this sea breeze is much more elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:16.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,186)\fnBradley Gratis\pos(351,330)\shad0\3c&H1E2118&\c&HFBFBFC&}Naval base at Kiel, in 1945
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:24.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So it's "Farewell Germany".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.87,0:02:29.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame that the last German sky we'll see is its usual leaden color.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:33.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to it, the Allies patrol over us has thinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:36.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we get past the Shetlands and out of the North Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:41.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,we'll soon be under Spain's blue sky, and then on to Africa's beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:45.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll soon miss these clouds, Lieutenant Colonel Matsuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.35,0:02:51.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After all, a man who's here to study aeronautics shouldn't be killed by a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.69,0:02:55.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And after coming all the way to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:59.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like we'll understand each other on this long trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:04.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to feel the same about that other passenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.08,0:03:06.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:10.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,the SS or SD, those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:20.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.34,0:03:24.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I really did have an elegant life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:30.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Life here just takes a dive when the car starts acting up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.19,0:03:34.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lun-san, is that new?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.61,0:03:35.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.86,0:03:40.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's too much. It's stolen too, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.70,0:03:44.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:48.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like anyone has anything to spare in their wallets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:53.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better pass, or Revy is going to crown me a wuss again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,0)\fnBradley Gratis\shad0\c&HFBFBFC&\pos(355,297)\3c&H492304&}Near the Cape Verde Islands, Africa 1945.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:16.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,King.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:28.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, please look forward to sea turtle soup tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:35.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,186)\fnBradley Gratis\shad0\3c&H1E2118&\c&HFBFBFC&\pos(357,347)}The Indian Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:37.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're moving with us at bearing 270.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:42.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Ceylon is now known as Sri Lanka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:42.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a freighter out of South Africa heading to Ceylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:42.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:45.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're in battle position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:46.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:51.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, but I want you to answer me one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.27,0:04:56.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to ignore your orders and attack that freighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.31,0:04:57.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:05:00.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you to Batavia without fail, Lieutenant Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:05:00.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Batavia is now known as Jakarta.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:01.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fritz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:02.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:06.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you even greet the enemy without confirmation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.20,0:05:08.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You call yourself this ship's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:09.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:13.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ready the rowing boat that's under maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.16,0:05:16.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Lieutenant Colonel, get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An attack would be a completely unnecessary risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:22.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is a transport of your life-long enemy, England.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:29.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's being carried is fuel for an invasion of the ally we'll soon be guests of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:31.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to ignore that enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:36.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was the point of our war so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:43.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sinking that ship will have no effect on our fatherland.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:46.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:48.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:55.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that you can't stop the setting sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:58.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to force me to say more?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:06:00.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was just surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:06.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were worrying about something more pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:07.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:11.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But there are battles that must be taken on, despite that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:12.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:14.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare the submerging torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:17.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Add a score of 31 to that ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:24.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Launcher is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:25.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:27.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We will keep fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:33.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to go drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:37.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After I calculate the fuel efficiency of the torpedo ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:40.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:42.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:43.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:46.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look like an off-season Santa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:49.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were looking at this at the shop, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:51.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:53.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You always act so reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:57.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you can't mean, is that for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:09.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy ship just passed over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:15.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,188)\fnBradley Gratis\shad0\c&HFBFBFC&\pos(353,328)\3c&H372C13&}Near the Nicobar Islands, Indonesia
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.87,0:07:21.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,188)\fs40\fnBradley Gratis\shad0\c&HFBFBFC&\pos(350,375)\3c&H5F661B&}March 25, 1945
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.63,0:07:26.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Set course to 2-0-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:29.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get behind the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.21,0:07:31.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we turn twice, we can get behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.93,0:07:33.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The second turn will be in four minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:35.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:40.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's another one in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.93,0:07:42.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And another signal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:45.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy coming out in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:48.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"We are being dominated..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:50.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With Batavia right in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:52.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:55.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Both engines full power. Set course to 1-7-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.28,0:07:56.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,1-7-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:58.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fire the Zigarren towards our rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:07:59.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Firing Zigarren.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.59,0:08:10.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One of the enemy ships is moving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.13,0:08:11.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They took the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:14.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop the ship. Silent running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:26.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One ship won't break away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:30.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's an active sonar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:31.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Full power to the engines!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:33.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Port 20 degrees! Set course to 40!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:08:52.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the forward torpedo room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.21,0:08:54.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're taking on water!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:56.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Close the hatch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:58.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Captain! Please take care of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:09.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've stopped taking on water as much as possible, but we can't blow the main tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:14.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Engines and the electric generator are damaged. Repairing either is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.57,0:09:20.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate that we couldn't return the Japanese to his homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:23.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Colonel Matsuda has already...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:26.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The way of the samurai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:31.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize he brought a katana for that end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:37.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Brave and loyal soldiers of Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:42.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We faced great opposition and rough waters in the Atlantic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:48.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but we will finish our final battle, without seeing the coconuts of Batavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:53.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Currently our ship has run aground at a depth of 57 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:56.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There is no promise that the ballast or engine will be repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:10:00.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have endured numerous battles with courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:04.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment I relieve you all of military duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:06.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In two hours our air will run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.75,0:10:09.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Choose freely how you wish to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:15.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Colonel, I have to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:19.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, I haven't heard the engine in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:21.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When will we surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:23.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We won't surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:25.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:29.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.65,0:10:31.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.23,0:10:32.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.52,0:10:33.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:35.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:36.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:38.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The importance of your mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:42.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning of this painting I carry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:46.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so the package was this painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:50.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look that impressive to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:51.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it titled?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:55.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"The Twelve Knights led by Brunhilda."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:11:01.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only piece that has been painted since the Führer took power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:06.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Steadfast in our honor and loyalty, hide this until the promised day."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.97,0:11:10.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"The day the Nazi flag flies again."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.98,0:11:16.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"This will be the guiding light for our comrades!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:21.41,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, we already know we are going to lose this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:25.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And we wanted to prepare for the next war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You people...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:31.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have family?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.75,0:11:34.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A wife and child in Stuttgart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:35.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:42.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am proud that I fought with all I had for the fatherland.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.05,0:11:45.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have no regrets, even now as I'm condemned to a watery grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.85,0:11:48.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, If I have one dissatisfaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:54.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,it's that I have to share a casket with a fuck-head like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:57.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,who can't even remember his family in his last moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.94,0:12:00.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take that statement back, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.40,0:12:04.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot compare family to the righteousness of country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.20,0:12:05.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:11.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you struggle, Hitler's empire is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:12.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:17.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By putting up with your obsession, my country and my navy ended up like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:18.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:25.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we've sunk, if my children never have to see that accursed Nazi flag ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:26.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.97,0:12:27.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:32.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our ship sinking may be the will of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:42.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:46.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Opening my mouth was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:49.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I only went scuba diving once at Ishigaki Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:52.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch tricked me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:56.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I've heard since we've left port.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:59.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be a little more amusing, you idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:05.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go salvaging!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.47,0:13:16.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I explained it at the office, but I'll go through the details again before we go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.02,0:13:17.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Benny, will you start?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:18.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:21.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,First, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:26.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An old story from an elderly gentleman from 50 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:30.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,IXC-type attack submarine U-1234 of the German navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:34.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A submarine in the Wolf Pack that tore up the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.04,0:13:38.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The captain was Major Venztel H. Aabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.29,0:13:47.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The last order he received from the falling homeland was to take a Japanese officer to Batavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But things weren't that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:52.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To get there, you need to go around Europe, then Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:55.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a voyage worthy of Magellan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:58.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But Aabe pulled it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:07.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But when he finally saw his destination, his ship and passenger suddenly ran out of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:11.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,While searching for the Japanese, the US Navy came across this U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:14.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because of their boredom, they all struck at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:18.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The poor U-1234 finally ran out of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.46,0:14:24.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The captain and 44 of his crew disappeared into the darkness of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:30.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Up to this point that's historical fact, but there's another, untold story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:34.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A story of an SS officer who appeared the night before departure from Keil Port,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.35,0:14:40.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and forced his way on board with papers from the secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.73,0:14:44.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:49.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the painting he held on to for his dear life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:53.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The artist was August Janke, an unknown painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:57.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The title is "The Twelve Knights led by Brunhilda".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:15:00.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks pretty fucking boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.37,0:15:03.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Graffiti on the New York Metro looks more exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:10.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why did an officer board a submarine with just one painting, with no gold or papers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:14.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:20.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an incredible story. As far as logic or reason, I don't have anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:26.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The one thing that we know is that this painting is sleeping on a sunken sub.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:29.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We have an order from a collector in Spain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:33.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His hobby is collecting Nazi art.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.28,0:15:35.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a weird hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:36.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.66,0:15:39.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Most of Janke's work was destroyed in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:44.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He had given up this, along with the U-boat. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:53.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But last year a French phone company laying down underwater cables discovered U-1234.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:56.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And without much water found inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:16:00.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In this area several countries are fighting for control.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:02.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one can make a go for it easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.65,0:16:06.11,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's where we come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:08.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A nice 50,000 dollar job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:11.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, these are the steps for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:13.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:18.62,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The French found that the bow end is completely watered in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:22.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The two of you will go in through the torpedo tubes and then shut them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.58,0:16:26.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you weld the hole shut first, you should be able to open the door from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.50,0:16:27.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Weld?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:29.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do on the way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:32.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just make a hole somewhere and swim out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:35.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get what we want, we don't need anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:38.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right then, let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:43.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't even done weekend carpentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:47.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And underwater too. This isn't gonna work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:50.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you done checking the equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:55.74,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep bitching, I'm throwing you in the sea without a tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.16,0:16:57.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:00.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about the buoyancy compensator? Did you test the gauge?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:04.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you drown, I'm leaving you down in that Nazi casket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.92,0:17:07.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so pissy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:08.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:11.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you die, you're gonna be in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.71,0:17:13.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So stop talking back, you idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:14.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:16.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After you dive, I'll only be able to track you with the beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.01,0:17:19.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So don't toast the batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:21.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:22.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A souvenir from Balalaika, when she went back to the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:28.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An underwater rifle? Does it go full-auto?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:31.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Take it as a protective charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.11,0:17:34.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,OK. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:35.95,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.41,0:17:45.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, you won her over with a gun and saved Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.87,0:17:47.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have a lot of tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:48.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:52.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As an employer, I worry about human relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:00.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The beacon's been activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:03.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The PLRS is working fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:03.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}PLRS: Position Location Reporting System.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:04.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:07.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They've headed straight for a hunk of metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.27,0:18:09.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revy must be used to this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:10.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.94,0:18:15.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't hire her, if all her tricks only involved guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.28,0:18:18.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's got a natural talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:20.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:35.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:36.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:38.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come up for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:39.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:40.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.89,0:18:42.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're not on a regular sea route.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.76,0:18:45.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If someone's out here, it's gotta be the cable company.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.31,0:18:46.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cable company?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:48.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:52.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After we got the offer I've been listening to their communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.44,0:18:54.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They shouldn't be out here for another three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:56.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that's a research ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:59.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's got big equipment on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:01.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:04.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Put up a Thai Navy flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:05.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:09.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To the stopped ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:11.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the White Heather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:13.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.29,0:19:15.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They want to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:20.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is PT377 of the Thai Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:22.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We are currently on a mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.68,0:19:25.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to inquire about your purpose in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:29.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us your nationality, ship number and signal code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:32.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We see that you are acting independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.56,0:19:34.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where is your ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:37.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is a military matter and I cannot answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.48,0:19:41.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I request your information one more time, over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.82,0:19:46.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They sure put a lot of pressure on ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:49.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:51.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to the control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:53.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Keep track of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:56.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like how the clouds are moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.09,0:19:57.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fold up your parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.34,0:19:59.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right. What do you want to do about those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:02.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As long as their beacon is on, we can get them any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.34,0:20:05.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Worst case scenario, we take care of those guys and pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:07.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hail Überführer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:14.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After checking on communications, there are no military vessels in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:19.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, they are hated bandits who are plundering this sacred grave-site.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:22.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is your verdict, Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:24.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.37,0:20:29.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The proof of inheritance of this grave-site is rightfully ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.20,0:20:31.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, Squad Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.21,0:20:34.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will allow destruction with an iron fist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.58,0:20:36.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:39.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch, they're moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.05,0:20:41.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,OK. I just started the engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:46.64,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:56.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2\fscx70\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}TOW: Tube-launched, Optically tracked, Wire-guided (US anti-tank missile).
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:56.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch! It's a TOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:20:56.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,God damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:20:58.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, they did it after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.82,0:21:01.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Benny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.95,0:21:09.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.49,0:21:11.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An anti-tank missile!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.33,0:21:14.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Run, run, degenerationists.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.21,0:21:17.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is our destined reunion with Brunhilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.75,0:21:19.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one will stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:34.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This underground grave is about to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.70,0:23:18.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to be one of us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.96,0:23:22.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, I'm going to kill you.
